<p>
  The Light / Dark theme is implemented with Css variables and a data attribute on <code>&lt;html&gt;</code>:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><code>&lt;html data-theme="light"&gt;</code></li>
  <li><code>&lt;html data-theme="dark"&gt;</code></li>
</ul>

<h2>Implementation</h2>

<p>
  Each component in <%= link_to raw("<code>hot_docs.css</code>"), "https://github.com/3v0k4/hot_docs/blob/main/app/assets/stylesheets/hot_docs.css" %> comes with variables for both themes.
</p>

<p>
  For example, the <code>.footer</code> styles start with:
</p>

<pre><code>:root {
  --footer-background-color: #e9e9e9;
}

[data-theme=dark]:root {
  --footer-background-color: #444444;
}</pre></code>
